In synchronous programming, operations are executed one after the other, waiting for each to complete before moving on. In asynchronous programming, operations can be performed concurrently, allowing multiple operations to execute at the same time.

Synchronous code:
```javascript
function syncFunction() {
  console.log('Step 1');
  const result = calculateSomething();
  console.log('Step 2', result);
}
```

Asynchronous code:
```javascript
async function asyncFunction() {
  console.log('Step 1');
  const promiseResult = await doSomethingAsync();
  console.log('Step 2', promiseResult);
}
```

