The total number of digits in a set of consecutive numbers can be calculated using the formula: 

$$
\begin{equation*}
\text{Total digits} = \lfloor 1 + \log_2(N) \rfloor,
\end{equation*}
$$

where $N$ is the last number in the set. 

In this case, we are given that the total number of digits is 1095. Solving for $N$, we get:

$$
\begin{align*}
1 + \log_2(N) & = 1095 \\
\log_2(N) & = 1094 \\
N & = 2^{1094}
\end{align*}
$$

